snippet.textDisplay:
Don't intend for this comment to emit offence or rudeness.


The photo shown in the segment of the 'bush fire' segment, is quite factually false. Surprisingly, the picture was not even published or released by Australia, and is a hyperbole - to say the least. Assuming that the red 'fire' icons are severe bush fires, we can see that around 55% of Australia is covered in pure Armageddon. THIS IS FALSE!


I live in Queensland, and it seems that at the date of posting (5 days after this video was released), that there are only 2 major fires occurring. Once again, I don't intent to strike a beat-up of any opinion. It just seems that other countries are seeing this in different ares than we are.


Nevertheless, my dearest support goes out to all affect by the blazes. To the hardest struck in Victoria, NSW, and Western Australian - we can make it.
